    • Constructor Detail

      • Phenomenon

        public Phenomenon(int id)
        The default constructor for this class. Sets the unique identifier for this phenomenon, and initializes all other fields to zero/ empty.
        The resulting phenomenon will be usable by the physics logic, but will not have a useful default state.

      • Phenomenon

        public Phenomenon(int id,
                  Point position,
                  int dx0,
                  int dy0,
                  int lifespan,
                  java.util.List<java.util.List<Point>> shapes)
        The comprehensive constructor for this class. Initializes a phenomenon described by the input parameters.
        Parameters:
        id - The unique identifier of the phenomenon.
        position - The starting position of the phenomenon.
        dx0 - The initial x velocity of the phenomenon.
        dy0 - The initial y velocity of the phenomenon.
        lifespan - The number of refresh cycles until the phenomenon will be discarded by the physics logic.
        shapes - A list of the possible shapes of this phenomenon.
